    "note": "Separation anxiety disorder is characterized by developmentally inappropriate and excessive fear or anxiety concerning separation from attachment figures. DSM-5 criteria require at least 3 of 8 symptoms lasting >4 weeks in children (adults: >6 months). Must be distinguished from normal separation anxiety which is developmentally appropriate in toddlers. CBT is first-line treatment. SSRIs are used for moderate-severe cases. School refusal is a common presentation requiring systematic assessment.",
